# Python line comments

Do not put **two or more** separate `# ...` segments on the same line of code (e.g. a `ty: ignore` plus a second explanatory `# ...`). Use **one** trailing `#` comment per line.

**Bad:**

```python
foo()  # ty: ignore[x]  # why this is needed
```

**Good:**

```python
# Why this is needed.
foo()  # ty: ignore[x]
```

If both a checker suppression and a human note are needed, put the explanation on the **previous** line as its own comment.
